<i>The lion sleeps tonight</i>

28:02.305 --> 28:06.476
<i>Weeheeheehee dee heeheeheehee</i>

28:06.559 --> 28:09.521
<i>Weeoh aweem away...</i>

28:10.230 --> 28:11.773
<i>Weeheeheehee</i>

28:12.065 --> 28:14.317
I'm a real explorer
if I have a slouch hat?

28:14.442 --> 28:16.736
-REMTULLA: Yeah, exactly.
-All right, so that... so... so...

28:16.820 --> 28:19.364
so it's like... it's like,
that's the vibe?

28:19.489 --> 28:22.450
<i>Weeheeheehee dee heeheeheehee</i>

28:22.534 --> 28:25.412
<i>Weeoh aweem away</i>

28:28.415 --> 28:29.666
(EXHALES)

28:33.253 --> 28:36.381
-(WILDEBEEST GRUMBLING)
-(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

28:37.215 --> 28:39.801
GEORGE: It looks good. You go first.

28:40.885 --> 28:42.387
WILL: I'm not gonna go first.
You go first.

28:42.470 --> 28:44.139
-GEORGE: No, you go first.
-REMTULLA: No, you go, you go.

28:44.222 --> 28:46.057
-REMTULLA: No, you go, you go.
-WILL: I'm right behind you.

28:46.141 --> 28:48.101
Just go ahead. I mean, you're already
standing there, just go ahead.

28:48.184 --> 28:49.644
Yeah, I got your back, man.

28:49.728 --> 28:52.105
(ALL LAUGH)

28:56.484 --> 29:00.071
WILL: <i>The single brain is saying,</i>
<i>"I don't want to get eaten."</i>

29:00.613 --> 29:05.326
But the swarm mind is saying,
"There's grass over there. Let's go."

29:07.078 --> 29:08.997
<i>It's a pressure cooker.</i>

29:15.670 --> 29:20.341
<i>Maybe what they really need</i>
<i>is one last push.</i>

29:22.302 --> 29:24.846
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

29:37.650 --> 29:41.613
<i>There are tiny dots of slime mold</i>
<i>almost everywhere.</i>

29:43.698 --> 29:48.203
<i>Most of the time,</i>
<i>slime mold just sits around,</i>

29:48.745 --> 29:52.749
<i>eating bacteria</i>
<i>and making more slime mold.</i>

29:54.292 --> 29:57.629
<i>But when these single-celled organisms</i>
<i>run out of food,</i>

29:59.339 --> 30:01.216
<i>something weird happens.</i>

30:07.931 --> 30:11.518
<i>Waves of restless energy</i>
<i>ripple through the swarm.</i>

30:13.269 --> 30:18.691
<i>They join themselves together</i>
<i>into a new creature.</i>

30:30.036 --> 30:32.831
<i>Many cells become one body.</i>

30:33.373 --> 30:38.378
<i>And then when the pressure</i>
<i>finally gets too much, they move.</i>

31:24.674 --> 31:26.301
<i>There's sacrifice involved.</i>

31:27.886 --> 31:32.056
<i>The long, thin stems</i>
<i>are created by cells dying.</i>

31:34.517 --> 31:37.604
<i>But they give the others</i>
<i>a chance to survive</i>

31:37.687 --> 31:42.942
<i>by being carried away to pastures new</i>
<i>when something brushes against them.</i>

31:47.572 --> 31:52.327
<i>Individually, these guys</i>
<i>are literally brainless,</i>

31:53.286 --> 31:56.915
<i>but together, they're smart.</i>

32:04.422 --> 32:09.135
<i>And wildebeest?</i>
<i>They're a bit like slime mold.</i>

32:10.803 --> 32:11.846
<i>No offense.</i>

32:27.362 --> 32:32.200
<i>Loads of individuals somehow</i>
<i>having to make a joint decision.</i>

32:32.909 --> 32:36.454
<i>Thousands of brains</i>
<i>slowly crunching the data.</i>

32:39.749 --> 32:41.584
(CROCODILE HISSING)

32:41.918 --> 32:43.378
<i>"Danger in front...</i>

32:45.880 --> 32:47.465
<i>"food running out behind."</i>

32:51.719 --> 32:54.389
<i>Waves of nervous energy building...</i>

32:57.225 --> 33:00.353
<i>that finally pushes them to the edge.</i>

33:03.648 --> 33:04.774
<i>-And an answer.</i>
-(MUSIC GETS QUIETER)

33:07.026 --> 33:10.321
(MUSIC CRESCENDOS)

33:10.530 --> 33:12.156
REMTULLA: They're going. Going.

33:12.991 --> 33:15.201
-WILL: They're gone. They're gone.
-GEORGE: They're going.

33:20.123 --> 33:21.249
Look at that.

33:28.631 --> 33:29.757
Oh, man.

33:30.800 --> 33:32.844
-All right, you got the...
-REMTULLA: They're crossing.

33:32.927 --> 33:34.679
-Get the bino...
-WILL: Thank you, thank you.

33:35.179 --> 33:38.099
(STAMPEDE RUNNING)

33:38.933 --> 33:41.477
(INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC)

34:39.243 --> 34:41.162
That's spectacular.

34:41.829 --> 34:43.206
(WILL LAUGHS)

34:48.211 --> 34:50.129
That looks crazy.

34:52.340 --> 34:54.008
-Wow. (LAUGHS)
-GEORGE: Wow.

34:55.510 --> 34:57.261
(WILDEBEESTS BLEAT)

34:59.097 --> 35:02.642
WILL: <i>I've had more than half my life</i>
<i>to get ready for this.</i>

35:02.850 --> 35:06.312
<i>But nothing prepares you for the dust,</i>

35:07.438 --> 35:11.400
<i>the noise, the sheer scale of it.</i>

35:19.450 --> 35:20.910
Wow!

35:24.455 --> 35:26.165
Hey, that... Once you commit...

35:27.291 --> 35:28.376
GEORGE: No turning back.

35:31.379 --> 35:34.257
All right, 30 years. That was
on my bucket list for like 30 years.

35:34.382 --> 35:36.384
We just got it,
the migration of the wildebeest,

35:36.467 --> 35:37.844
the crossing of the river.

35:38.261 --> 35:40.972
We have done what we have come to done.

35:43.141 --> 35:47.728
<i>Thousands and thousands</i>
<i>of individual organisms</i>

35:48.980 --> 35:52.316
<i>surviving by joining together.</i>

35:53.151 --> 35:57.155
<i>The swarm drives them and protects them.</i>

35:59.740 --> 36:01.742
<i>Not everyone can make it.</i>

36:05.746 --> 36:07.623
<i>But most of them do.</i>

36:14.797 --> 36:18.968
<i>Look at them go.</i>
<i>It's like they're tied together.</i>

36:19.218 --> 36:22.680
<i>You can, like...</i>
<i>You can feel the connection.</i>

36:27.393 --> 36:28.978
So it looks like, even from...

36:30.771 --> 36:33.900
What could be a quarter mile away,
that they know.

36:35.318 --> 36:40.823
Like these all the way back here,
can sense what's happening up here.

36:47.955 --> 36:53.753
<i>For almost 30 years,</i>
<i>I've had an image in my mind.</i>

36:58.090 --> 37:02.220
<i>The plains of Africa dense</i>
<i>with millions of wildebeest.</i>

37:03.262 --> 37:07.225
But in the end,
I saw something I wasn't expecting.

37:07.934 --> 37:10.686
It's not millions of animals at all.

37:12.939 --> 37:14.357
<i>It's just one.</i>

37:14.690 --> 37:16.984
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

37:25.326 --> 37:28.371
Like George said, shift your perspective,

37:30.414 --> 37:31.832
<i>switch your lens,</i>

37:33.251 --> 37:37.213
<i>and you'll see the swarm everywhere.</i>

37:47.807 --> 37:52.311
<i>Makes you wonder,</i>
<i>do they even know they're in a swarm?</i>

37:54.063 --> 37:56.607
<i>Come to think of it, do we?</i>

38:00.069 --> 38:02.863
Damn. Now, that's a question.

38:05.157 --> 38:06.534
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

38:06.784 --> 38:09.954
<i>Next, I'm on the trail</i>
<i>of a deadly predator.</i>

38:10.037 --> 38:11.122
MALE VOICE: <i>Shark!</i>

38:11.998 --> 38:14.041
-Whoa, there he is.
-Mm-hmm, you got one.

38:14.250 --> 38:16.043
WILL: Aw, yeah.

38:17.628 --> 38:21.465
<i>Following my nose to solve</i>
<i>a desert island mystery.</i>

38:21.716 --> 38:24.010
Whoa, that is gorgeous.

38:24.844 --> 38:29.181
<i>And discover that smell</i>
<i>is not what it seems.</i>

38:36.522 --> 38:38.649
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
